Ansible ======= (Powerful automation platform tool)
 - configuration management tool (CM tool)
      - provisioning tool (like terraform)
      - CI/CD deployment
      - Network automation
 - Competitors - CHEF, puppet, salt-stack
 - Agentless, push style, idempotance
 - Modules written in python 
 - connectivity (ssh - linux, winrm - windows)
 - ansible tower - GUI (RBAC - users restriction)
 - playbooks (collection of plays - tasks) in YAML
 - managed node should have python
 - Control node should be LINUX like or it can be windows with WSL installed.

Getting started
 - Python installed > Install ansible of control node > setup passwordless auth. with managed nodes > create inventory file > configure ansible.cfg



